How many times does the body of the following loop execute?

```java
for (int i = 3; i <= 9; i++) {
    System.out.println(i);
}
```

What is the output of the following code?

```java
String result = "";
for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
    result += i;
}
System.out.println(result);
```

What are the values of `x` and `count` after the following code executes?

```java
int x = 1;
int count = 0;
while (x < 20) {
    x *= 3;
    count++;
}
```

How many times is `count++` executed when the following code runs?

```java
int count = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
        count++;
    }
}
```

What output is produced by the following code?

```java
for (int i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
    for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
        System.out.print("* ");
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```

How many times does the body of the following loop execute?

```java
for (int k = 2; k <= 14; k += 3) {
    System.out.println(k);
}
```

What is the value of `total` after the following code executes?

```java
int total = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
    if (i % 2 == 0) {
        total += i;
    }
}
```

What are the values of `a` and `b` after the following code executes?

```java
int a = 20;
int b = 1;
while (a > b) {
    a -= 4;
    b += 3;
}
```

What is the value of `count` after the following code executes?

```java
int count = 0;
for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    for (int j = 1; j < i; j++) {
        count++;
    }
}
```

